     @{" 1 " LINK LoadSave} Load/Save

     @{" 2 " LINK Learn} Learn

     @{" 3 " LINK ShowAgain} Show again
@ENDNODE

@NODE BBLib "The BBLib Menu"
@TOC Menus

       When BootX is started it will look for a ${"file" LINK GlossaryF} called @{"BootX.BBLib" LINK GlossaryB}.
     This @{"Bootblock library" LINK GlossaryB} contains custom @{"bootblocks" LINK GlossaryB} that you can use
     instead of the standard @{"OldFileSystem" LINK GlossaryO} or @{"FastFileSystem" LINK GlossaryF}
     bootblocks.

       With the Bootblock library system you can create several different
     libraries that contain your collection games, demo or utility
     bootblocks.  The libraries are much easier to maintain than
     several single files.  If one of your autobooting game or demo
     @{"disks" LINK GlossaryD} get infected by a @{"bootvirus" LINK GlossaryB}, you can always use the copy you
     saved in your library to restore the disk.

       You can install any bootblock in the library by selecting it using
     the 'Show installable bootblock' gadget and then @{"clicking" LINK GlossaryC} on the
     'Install' gadget.

     @{" 1 " LINK BBLibNew} New

     @{" 2 " LINK BBLibLoad} Load

     @{" 3 " LINK BBLibSave} Save

     @{" 4 " LINK BBLibShow} Show

     @{" 5 " LINK BBLibMerge} Merge

     @{" 6 " LINK BBLibAdd} Add bootblock

     @{" 7 " LINK BBLibDelete} Delete bootblock

     @{" 8 " LINK BBLibRename} Rename bootblock
@ENDNODE

@NODE Brain "The Brain Menu"
@TOC Menus

       At startup time BootX looks for a file called @{"BootX.Brain" LINK GlossaryB}.  This
     Brainfile contains all the bootblocks you have taught BootX using
     the Bootblock/Learn @{"menu item" LINK GlossaryM}.

       This Brainfile complements the knowledge base of BootX by letting
     BootX recognize any new bootblock that are not yet recognized by
     the @{"BootX.Recog" LINK GlossaryR} file.

                                   NOTE

          If you find new bootblocks that BootX does not yet
          recognize please send them to me so that I can update
          the Recog file. BootX will always give precedence to
          the conclusion of the Recog file when it tries to
          recognize a bootblock.  

     @{" 1 " LINK BrainNew} New

     @{" 2 " LINK BrainLoad} Load

     @{" 3 " LINK BrainSave} Save

     @{" 4 " LINK BrainShow} Show

     @{" 5 " LINK BrainMerge} Merge

     @{" 6 " LINK BrainDelete} Delete Brain cell

     @{" 7 " LINK BrainRename} Rename Brain cell
@ENDNODE

@NODE Preferences "The Preferences Menu"
@TOC Menus

     Want to change your preferences ? Look here for help:

     @{" 1 " LINK PrefEdit} Edit

