@NODE About "About BootX"
@TOC Main

       BootX is a powerful viruskiller for the Commodore-Amiga computer.
     It is fast (written completely in @{"assembler" LINK GlossaryA}) and tries to be as
     user friendly as possible.

       This program is freeware, this means that you can copy it
     freely as long as you don't ask any more money for it than a
     nominal fee for copying.  If you want to distribute this program
     you should keep this document with it.  This program cannot be
     used for commercial purposes without written permission from the
     author.  

       Special permission is hereby granted to include BootX in
     Public-Domain collections such as Fred Fish's Amiga Library.  

       BootX software and documentation are © 1989, 1990, 1991, 1992, 1993
     by Peter Stuer. All rights reserved.  
@ENDNODE

@NODE Requirements "System requirements"
@TOC Main

       BootX should run on any Amiga system with at least @{"512K" LINK GlossaryK} @{"RAM" LINK GlossaryR} and
     one disk drive. BootX requires @{"KickStart" LINK GlossaryK} v2.04 or higher to run. If
     BootX is run with @{"Workbench" LINK GlossaryW} v2.1 or higher it will use the
     @{"locale.library" LINK GlossaryL} to become language independent. Special care has been
     taken in the program design to make the program work with 68020,
     68030 and 68040 @{"processors", LINK GlossaryP} without sacrificing 68000
     compatibility.

       Should you have any trouble running BootX on your machine, please
     write to me with the full specifications of your machine, that is
     KickStart version, model, expansion boards etc...

       BootX also requires the @{"ReqTools.library" LINK GlossaryR} v38 or higher.  ReqTools
     is copyrighted 1992, 1993 by Nico François.

       If you want to save and load files that have been @{"crunched" LINK GlossaryC} with
     PowerPacker you will also need the @{"PowerPacker.library" LINK GlossaryP} v35 or
     higher.  PowerPacker is copyrighted 1992, 1993 by Nico François.

       To decrunch Library Imploded files during a file check you'll need
     the Explode.library v6.0 or higher.

       To use the help feature BootX requires the AmigaGuide.library to
     display the BootX.guide. This library comes with WorkBench 3.0.
@ENDNODE

@NODE Author "About the author and the program"
@TOC Main

       Since so many people keep asking me about it...  I graduated in
     June 1991 as a programmer-analyst.  BootX was created because at
     the time (April 1989) I did not trust the available viruskillers.
     In those days only the SCA and the Byte Bandit @{"bootviruses" LINK GlossaryB}
     where a threat to our @{"bootblocks" LINK GlossaryB}.

       If you have suggestions or remarks about this program, or if you
     find any @{"bugs" LINK GlossaryB}, please let me know.  If you find any new viruses or
     @{"linkviruses" LINK GlossaryL} that BootX does not recognize yet, please send them on
     a disk to me (@{"my address" LINK Addresses} follows this paragraph).  I will return
     the disk to you with an updated copy of BootX.

       When sending in @{"bug" LINK GlossaryB} reports, please state exactly under what
     circumstances the bug occurred, what equipment was used and what
     happened.  If possible also try to give me enough information to
     reproduce the bug.  It is very difficult to find bugs when you
     don't know exactly what happened.


     Write to one of the following addresses:

                SHI Safe Hex International
                Erik Loevendahl Soerensen
                Snaphanevej 10
                4720 Praestoe
                Denmark - Europe

                Phone: +45 55992512


@ENDNODE

